::Shadow Wing::

She dipped and rose again in the air.  She kept up pretty well.  She felt 
the predator in her rising to the surface.  She saw him as her target.  She 
beat her wings harder and came within a few feet of him.
"Oh I'm beast enough all right."  She grinned. Her spark raced at the 
challange.  She was about to touch him when a gust of wind caught her and 
she rose a little too high to touch him.  She beat wing and flew after him.  
She was having fun.  This was a test of her endurance and skill.  At the 
same time, she was enjoying the freedom of it all.

"And when I tag you, your cooking dinner tonight." She knew that aminals 
didn't cook thier food, but she wanted to rib him back a little.  She wanted 
to see if he could take what he dished out.

Lunarpine knew Shadow Wing had the advantage in tne air, all he could
do to avoid her was stay in the high grass and trees, he tried to
keep her upwind so he could smell her. She swept low, he moved to the
side, trying his damndest to stay ahead of her. In the wild the beast
had to stay ahead of the hunter, or end up lunch. Even though they
were only playing, he had to be a wolf, in both actions and reactions.

"Catch me if you can Wing, If you're beast enough." Lunarpine had to
rattle her chains a little, if she couldn't handle a little ribbing
then she couldn't handle a real fight. The soldier in him had to know
for sure who he could depend on when the firefight began.
